<font color="#FF0000">REFLECTIONS ON VIET NAM</font><br>
<tt>Sat Feb 22 10:07:09 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was stationed at Chu-Lai, in the support command, a musician in the band. I didn't have to go on patrols or fire a weapon so did not experience the pain so many found there. I played music for the &quot;in country R &amp; R troops&quot;, as they arrived and in a small jazz combo in the evenings. The combo was also flown around to different hills to entertain the field troops. I feel like I did my part to support the troops in Nam.<br>
As far as our purpose for being there, none except political. It was a political war to stop communism. Nothing more. I feel that we should have supported Ho Chi Min when we first took over from the French, held national elections and supported the will of the people. It couldn't have been as bad as what happened with the war.<br>
I pray for all the lost and hurt people from that war. 
